@startuml seq_quart_lista_missioni
' SPDX-License-Identifier: CC-BY-SA-4.0
title Sequenza: Lista MissionAssignment via Web App (async)

actor Browser
participant "AssignmentRouteHandler\n(Web App)" as Handler
participant "ACLMiddleware" as ACL
participant "AssignmentService" as Service
participant "MissionAssignmentRepository" as Repo
database "Persistenza" as STORE

Browser -> Handler : GET /missions/<mid>/assignments?status=IN_PROGRESS
activate Handler

Handler -> ACL : is_allowed(operatore, LIST, MISSION:*)
activate ACL
ACL --> Handler : ALLOWED (operatore in g.operator)
deactivate ACL

Handler -> Service : await list(mission_id,\n  filters={status:"IN_PROGRESS"})
activate Service

Service -> Repo : await list(filters)
activate Repo
Repo -> STORE : recupera assignment filtrati\nper missione e stato
STORE --> Repo : dati assignment
Repo --> Service : List[MissionAssignment]
deactivate Repo

Service --> Handler : List[AssignmentDTO]
deactivate Service

Handler --> Browser : 200 OK\n[ { id, mission_id,\n    assignee_type, assignee_id,\n    status, objectives }, ... ]
deactivate Handler

note over Handler, STORE
  La Web App gestisce ogni richiesta in modo asincrono.
  L'event loop gestisce l'I/O verso la persistenza senza bloccare.
  Permette alta concorrenza con un singolo processo.
end note

@enduml
